thing like me it strikes just when you finally get up to do something, suddenly every distraction in the world shows up. &nbsp; “I’m a bit thirsty, just a [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.0833333333333335,"src":"/static/432fdc064b9dc846680eeea2c5004c91/3b7c4/resistance.jpg","srcSet":"/static/432fdc064b9dc846680eeea2c5004c91/03841/resistance.jpg 250w,\n/static/432fdc064b9dc846680eeea2c5004c91/26396/resistance.jpg 500w,\n/static/432fdc064b9dc846680eeea2c5004c91/3b7c4/resistance.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}}},"categories":[{"name":"Running"}],"tags":null}},{"node":{"id":"6d5fda42-6c68-5299-8275-6e9f8716765e","slug":"goal-setting-are-you-being-realistic","template":"","format":"standard","title":"Goal Setting – Are You Being Realistic?","date":"2016-03-15T11:00:21.000Z","excerpt":"<p>Setting yourself goals when running is a brilliant way to stay motivated and make sure you build on positive habits. Unfortunately many runners are unrealistic with their goal setting and end up risking injury, or giving up in frustration! Knowing what kind of goals to set, and knowing how to see what goals are unrealistic are [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.0833333333333335,"src":"/static/deb9a8ce63dbd6305d106b1c53c9c307/3b7c4/goal.jpg","srcSet":"/static/deb9a8ce63dbd6305d106b1c53c9c307/03841/goal.jpg 250w,\n/static/deb9a8ce63dbd6305d106b1c53c9c307/26396/goal.jpg 500w,\n/static/deb9a8ce63dbd6305d106b1c53c9c307/3b7c4/goal.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}}},"categories":[{"name":"Running"}],"tags":null}},{"node":{"id":"708bb821-ca3a-5833-8922-d8698dda9a39","slug":"the-three-biggest-running-form-mistakes","template":"","format":"standard","title":"The Three Biggest Running Form Mistakes","date":"2016-03-01T10:00:51.000Z","excerpt":"<p>For many, the beauty of running is the simplicity. Back to basics, two feet on the ground, run to clear your head. Unfortunately if your technique is wrong, each run will feel like a chore and  your body will be less efficient. &nbsp; There are hundreds of articles and posts that will try and walk [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.0833333333333335,"src":"/static/a290c5f2f126407b6289994a1b752168/3b7c4/mistake.jpg","srcSet":"/static/a290c5f2f126407b6289994a1b752168/03841/mistake.jpg 250w,\n/static/a290c5f2f126407b6289994a1b752168/26396/mistake.jpg 500w,\n/static/a290c5f2f126407b6289994a1b752168/3b7c4/mistake.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}}},"categories":[{"name":"Running"}],"tags":null}},{"node":{"id":"fdb60ebc-4ddc-5b7b-9a8e-483352160a17","slug":"3-ways-to-run-faster","template":"","format":"standard","title":"3 Ways to Run Faster","date":"2016-01-25T10:30:51.000Z","excerpt":"<p>We all want to run that little bit faster, and a study published in the Journal of Strength and Conditioning Research shows that runners on average have got faster over the past decade. Although changing your running style takes time, you can introduce changes right away to improve your speed. &nbsp; Intervals Although you may [&hellip;]</p>\n","featured_media":{"localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.0833333333333335,"src":"/static/05fa0ad22fbe02e99ec123a2338da32d/3b7c4/three-ways.jpg","srcSet":"/static/05fa0ad22fbe02e99ec123a2338da32d/03841/three-ways.jpg 250w,\n/static/05fa0ad22fbe02e99ec123a2338da32d/26396/three-ways.jpg 500w,\n/static/05fa0ad22fbe02e99ec123a2338da32d/3b7c4/three-ways.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"}}}},"categories":[{"name":"Running"}],"tags":null}},{"node":{"id":"099ae931-5fbf-5690-8148-c679b17b745c","slug":"hit-2016-running-a-4-point-plan-to-get-you-started","template":"","format":"standard","title":"Hit 201